Mail on Sunday is the debut album by the American hip hop artist Flo Rida and 
was released on March 18, 2008 via Atlantic and Poe Boy. It spawned 3 
singles, the first, "Low" was #1 on the U.S. Billboard Hot 100 for 10 weeks. 
The second and third singles, "Elevator" and "In the Ayer" were modest hits 
as well, being Top 40 hits. "Roll" (featuring Sean Kingston) wasn&#039;t an official 
single, but it managed to peak at number 59 on the U.S. Billboard Hot 100, 
and number 43 on the Canadian Hot 100 due to digital sales in both 
countries.
